Name: tungiasis
Definition: A parasitic ectoparasitic infectious disease that is an inflammatory skin disease caused by the parasitic infestation of the female chigoe flea

Name: obsolete Ancylostoma caninum ancylostomiasis
Definition: A parasitic ectoparasitic infectious disease that is an inflammatory skin disease caused by the parasitic infestation of the female chigoe flea

Name: leech infestation
Definition: A parasitic ectoparasitic infectious disease that involves parasitic infestation by members of the subclass Hirudinea. The leeches remain attached to their hosts and feed on blood until they become full

Name: myiasis
Definition: A parasitic ectoparasitic infectious disease that is caused by parasitic dipterous fly larvae (maggots) feeding on the host's necrotic or living tissue.

Name: tick infestation
Definition: A parasitic ectoparasitic infectious disease that involves parasitic infestation of blood feeding ticks of the families Ixodidae and Argasidae on animals and humans. Ticks are vectors of a number diseases

Name: obsolete bovine tuberculosis
Definition: A parasitic ectoparasitic infectious disease that involves parasitic infestation of blood feeding ticks of the families Ixodidae and Argasidae on animals and humans. Ticks are vectors of a number diseases

Name: lice infestation
Definition: A parasitic ectoparasitic infectious disease that involves infestation of lice

Name: mite infestation
Definition: A parasitic ectoparasitic infectious disease that involves infestation of mites belonging to the family Sarcoptidae
